In a speech delivered at the State Dining Room, Vice President Kamala Harris highlighted the importance of building a strong and sustainable military force to address global threats to climate, health, physical security, and cyber security. She introduced General Jacqueline Van Ovost, Commander of the Air Mobility Command, and Lieutenant General Laura Richardson, Commanding General of United States Army North, praising their leadership and expertise. On International Women's Day, Harris acknowledged the contributions of women throughout history in defending the nation and emphasized the need to recruit, retain, and advance more women in the military. She stated that women currently make up 16 percent of active-duty military and 19 percent of enlisted officers, and that increasing their representation will make the nation safer. Harris concluded by congratulating General Van Ovost and Lieutenant General Richardson and introducing President Joe Biden.